values: This is a test post from Photobucket.com

I use a pic request from and try to reactivate my LJ. (HaHa - actually it was never really active before. xD Whatever. ;)) At the moment I have only old blurry or dark pics of Jolie, but I hope it's okay to get the idea about her look. I like how she looks with this wig, too - the color and the style - but I guess I have to find another wig, because I'm not really happy with the quality. A little frizzy, sometimes a little kind of greasy looking (especially with the old cam XD) and the cap is a bit loose. But all is better as being bald for a girl like Jolie. XD

You should visit Sock first, if you don't know Part I - although this mini-fic work from both sides we think. ;) Meanwhile in the living room - Fenris (moaning): "Kiki?" Kiki (nuzzling her overeated tummy): "Yes?" Fenris: *BUUURP* Both: *crazy giggle* ------------------------------------------------------------------- Note: Thank you very much Anna, for a lot of yummy fun again from Jen, Kiki, Fen and Pep! ;) Personal note from Pep: I would sell my grandmother for the possibility to buy reese stuff so easy in shops here, if only I still had a grandmother. ;) You see, you made a junkie of me - a reese junkie! Thank you for beeing our dealer Anna!:D
Birthday Wishes from my Gang =) *birthday hugs for best friend in universe*

In February I have bought a OOAK cross-necklace from Lindis (Little Necks) - perfect service, and I love this cross so much. Thanks to Linda. ;) Unfortunately, the camera in this flat makes only photos which frustrate us the most time. I should reactivate my analog reflex camera, but then we have to pay for the photos, we have to scan them, blablabla .. It's so easy with digital camera, but with this camera it's more annoying than easy. Okay try to think pink like Kiki;): Better a stinkeroo cam then no cam. ;)

Some photos of Sawyer. Sawyer is the newest additon to the gang (Only one more is allowed by myself. ;) ) - got her at the beginning of the month. She is a real tomboy and of course she loves pirates and pirates-stuff. ;) Her personal fad: She insists on wearing pirate-scarfs, patches and pants which are not long enough. I have no idea how you say "Hochwasser-Hose" in English. LOL) Bratz-Boyz Clothes are made for her. ;) We (yogigum and me) love this hairdo, but Sawyer don't like it so much. She's of another opinion: Way too girlish! And she told us she is no feather duster. LOL Sawyer and her buddy Fenris - and the pets. Best buds,too. ;)
